.TH "sys_statx" 9 "sys_statx" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
sys_statx \- System call to get enhanced stats
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "long" sys_statx
.BI "(int dfd "  ","
.BI "const char __user * filename "  ","
.BI "unsigned flags "  ","
.BI "unsigned int mask "  ","
.BI "struct statx __user * buffer "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dfd" 12
Base directory to pathwalk from *or* fd to stat.
.IP "filename" 12
File to stat or "" with AT_EMPTY_PATH
.IP "flags" 12
AT_* flags to control pathwalk.
.IP "mask" 12
Parts of statx struct actually required.
.IP "buffer" 12
Result buffer.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Note that \fBfstat\fP can be emulated by setting dfd to the fd of interest,
supplying "" as the filename and setting AT_EMPTY_PATH in the flags.
